# FORMS OF INVESTMENT ANALYSIS  
There are the following forms of investment analysis:  
- fundamental analysis;
- monetary analysis;
- technical analysis;
- the intuitive approach.

# 8.1.1 Money Supply Policy  
It is correct to argue that growth of the money supply can become inadequate if the only action taken by the monetary authorities is to lower interest rates. It is nevertheless wholly within the power of a government to ensure adequate growth of broad money. The government can print money to offset any fall in fountain-pen money. Chapters 9 and 10 contain a full explanation. The point here is that a government can employ debt management to increase its borrowing from banks. Listed in order of aggressiveness, it can:  
- reduce the sales of its own debt, below that needed to cover its net cash requirement;1  
- buy back bonds that it has issued previously;
- extend the range of bonds that it buys, to include, for example, corporate bonds;
